# Frontend Conventions

## Map Stack
- **deck.gl** — GPU-accelerated data visualization layers (GeoJsonLayer, PolygonLayer)
- **MapLibre GL JS** — base map renderer (NOT Mapbox — no API key needed)
- **react-map-gl** — React wrapper for MapLibre
- Free base map tiles: `https://basemaps.cartocdn.com/gl/dark-matter-gl-style/style.json` (dark mode)

## Design
- Dark mode UI (slick, modern look)
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Smooth transitions, loading skeletons
- Desktop-first (tablet secondary)

## Map Colors
| Classification | Color | Hex |
|----------------|-------|-----|
| SUBDIVIDABLE_MULTIPLE (3+ lots) | Bright green | #22c55e |
| SUBDIVIDABLE_STANDARD (2 lots) | Green | #4ade80 |
| SUBDIVIDABLE_SMALL_LOT | Teal | #2dd4bf |
| NEEDS_GEOMETRY | Yellow | #facc15 |
| AT_MINIMUM / TOO_SMALL | Light gray | #e5e7eb20 |
| Proposed lot lines | Blue dashed | #3b82f6 |
| Proposed structures | Orange | #f97316 |
| Existing buildings | Dark gray | #6b7280 |

## Performance
- deck.gl handles 120k+ polygons at 60fps via GPU
- Fetch parcels by viewport bbox (debounced on map move)
- Don't load all 120k parcels at once — use spatial filtering via API
